    "causal_summary": "The deep review found a cluster of single-writer / durability defects across the embedding-stack launcher + supervision + WAL surfaces. The handover mandates they land as ONE coordinated packet with a deterministic two-process concurrency test — not piecemeal — because they share resources (respawn lock, root-liveness authority, leases, shutdown marker) and piecemeal fixes re-collide. This is the highest-blast-radius surface in the repo (the program exists because of a DB-corruption incident here), so each finding must be re-validated at HEAD before editing.",
